# CLI Skill Maintenance

Use `skills-seed cli-skills` only to maintain this global `skills-seed-cli` operation Skill.

This is separate from project/workspace Skills generated by `skills-seed generate skills`.

## Targets

`--target, -t` accepts:

- `auto`: default. Manage only detected available targets.
- `claude`: manage Claude only.
- `codex`: manage Codex only.
- `all`: explicitly manage both Claude and Codex.

`auto` detects a target when the corresponding global directory exists or the executable is on PATH.

## `skills-seed cli-skills install`

Purpose:

- Install or update the global CLI operation Skill tree.

Examples:

- Auto-detected targets: `skills-seed cli-skills install`
- Claude only: `skills-seed cli-skills install --target claude`
- Codex only: `skills-seed cli-skills install --target codex`
- Force both targets: `skills-seed cli-skills install --target all`

Safety:

- Missing selected targets are created.
- Selected `skills-seed-cli` targets are fully rebuilt, replacing existing contents.

## `skills-seed cli-skills uninstall`

Purpose:

- Remove generated global CLI operation Skill directories.

Examples:

- Auto-detected targets: `skills-seed cli-skills uninstall`
- Claude only: `skills-seed cli-skills uninstall --target claude`
- Codex only: `skills-seed cli-skills uninstall --target codex`
- Both targets: `skills-seed cli-skills uninstall --target all`

Safety:

- Selected `skills-seed-cli` target directories are removed regardless of their current contents.
- Parent agent Skills directories are not removed.

## Metadata

`SKILL.md` records source and version metadata:

- `generated-by: skills-seed`
- `skills-seed-version`
- `prompt-templates-sha256`
- `skills-templates-sha256`

Use `skills-seed --version` to compare installed metadata with the current binary.
